title: Top ranked WNCC volleyball team continues to roll
text:
Top ranked WNCC volleyball team continues to roll Cougars winners of twelve matches in a row Large Text WNCC vs Northeastern (volleyball) 
For the first time in the regular season since 2011. The Western Nebraska Community College volleyball team is ranked number one in the entire country. More from KOTA Territory 
The Cougars withstood its first test as the No. 1 team in the nation Wednesday night at Cougar Palace, but it wasn’t easy as they downed Northeastern Junior College in four grueling games 25-23, 22-25, 25-19, 25-18 to remain perfect in the South Division with a 5-0 mark. 
Set one saw the Cougars roar out to a big lead only to see NJC rally to close the gap. In the end WNCC picked up the first set winning 25-23.Northeastern answered earning the second set in a close.After that the Cougars picked up sets three and four to pick up the win. 
For WNCC, Fabiana Andrade had 15 kills to lead the Cougars while Kaio-Perez had 10 kills. Fautino Manu and Barbara Rabanal each had six, while Jady Gerott and Katy Ernest each had three. 
Andrade also tallied 40 set assists along with seven points and two aces. Rabanal finished with eight points, while Ernest, Santanna Mitchell, and Shaney Tiumalu each had two. 
WNCC finished with eight aces on the night. Including an ace on Ernest’s match point. 
The win over NJC improves WNCC’s record to 25–3 and they are winners of twelve in a row. 
Wednesday’s contest was also Pawzitively Pink Night at Cougar Palace. Everyone was asked to wear pink for Breast Cancer Awareness Month. 
Cougars will return to action on Friday at home as they are hosting a two day invite.WNCC will face Western Texas and Garden City Friday and then McCook and Casper on Saturday.
